The paper discusses meta-learning algorithms for model-based reinforcement learning in robotics, which involves both machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence algorithms for robotics, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves control systems, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves computer vision for robotic tasks, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
